{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/weburl\/percentencoding"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":1},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WebURL"}],"title":"Percent-Encoding and Decoding","role":"collectionGroup"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL"],"title":"Parsing and Manipulating URLs"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncoding"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Encode Data for a URL, or Decode Data from a URL."}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/formEncoding"],"title":"Percent-Encoding Sets"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentEncoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions"],"title":"Encoding and Decoding Lazily"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"What-is-Percent-Encoding?","text":"What is Percent-Encoding?","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Because URLs are a string format, certain characters may have special meaning depending on their position:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for example, a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\/\""},{"text":" in the path is used to separate the path’s segments, and the first ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"?\""},{"text":" in the URL","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"marks the start of the query section. This poses an interesting question:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"What if I have a path component that contains a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"literal"}]},{"text":" forward-slash?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC\/DC\" ","\/\/                                 ^","\/\/            \"AC\/DC\" should be a single component!"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When these situations occur, we need to encode (or “escape”) the slash in our path component,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so it won’t be confused with the path delimiters. URLs use a form of encoding called "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"percent-encoding","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because it encodes binary data using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"%XX\""},{"type":"text","text":" strings, where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XX"},{"type":"text","text":" is a hexadecimal byte value."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the ASCII forward-slash character, the byte value is "},{"code":"2F","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", so the URL shown above would become:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","\/\/                                 ^^^ 😌"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Percent-encoding is particularly important when building strings for URL components at runtime, because it means that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"even ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"\/\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"?\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" characters in user input won’t be confused with path delimiters or other characters with special","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"meaning to the URL. Additionally, since percent-encoding always produces an ASCII string, we can use it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to encode Unicode text in URLs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["func urlForProfile(_ username: String) -> WebURL {","  var url  = WebURL(\"https:\/\/example.com\/\")!  ","  url.path = \"\/accounts\/\" + username.percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet) + \"\/profile\"","  return url","}","","urlForProfile(\"BakerAli88\") ","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/BakerAli88\/profile\"","urlForProfile(\"AC\/DC??\")","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/AC%2FDC%3F%3F\/profile\"                             ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"Günther\")    ","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/G%C3%BCnther\/profile\"                            ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"🦆\")","\/\/ ✅ \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/%F0%9F%A6%86\/profile\"","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since URL components are percent-encoded, their contents must be recovered by decoding.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let url = WebURL(\"https:\/\/%F0%9F%A6%86@example.com\/\")!","url.username                  \/\/ \"%F0%9F%A6%86\" - Who's that?","url.username.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"🦆\" - Oh..."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Remember - percent encoding exists so that URL components have an unambiguous structure.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you decode a component’s value too early or too many times, you may introduce bugs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The following example demonstrates this with two approaches to split a path string in to its components.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let url = urlForBand(\"AC\/DC\") ","\/\/ \"https:\/\/example.com\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"                              ","\/\/                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^","","\/\/ The Right Way: Split, then decode each component.","let rawPath = url.path \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","let rawPathComponents = rawPath.split(\"\/\").map { $0.percentDecoded() }","\/\/ ✅ [\"bands\", \"AC\/DC\"]","","\/\/ The Wrong Way: Decode the entire path, then split.","let decodedPath = url.path.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC\/DC\"","let decodedPathComponents = decodedPath.split(\"\/\")","\/\/ ❌ [\"bands\", \"AC\", \"DC\"]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Working with percent-encoded path strings can be tricky. We recommend leaving it to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL\/pathComponents-swift.property","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" view wherever possible."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Data is encoded using a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that informs the encoder which characters are allowed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the resulting string. The URL Standard defines some encode-sets, and you can define your own."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Extensions-to-Standard-Library-Types","text":"Extensions to Standard Library Types","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"WebURL provides a number of extensions to standard library types to aid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in encoding or decoding percent-encoded data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Encoding-Text-or-Binary-Data","text":"Encoding Text or Binary Data","type":"heading","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String.percentEncoded(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Collection.percentEncodedString(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To percent-encode a String, call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentEncoded(using:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function and specify an encode-set to use."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet"},{"type":"text","text":" is usually a good choice for arbitrary strings:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it includes all URL special characters, and encodes some additional characters to match the JavaScript function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"encodeURIComponent"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you have binary data, you can call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentEncodedString(using:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function, which is available"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on all collections of bytes, to produce a percent-encoded ASCII string of its contents."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\"AC\/DC\".percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"AC%2FDC\"","Data(...).percentEncodedString(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"%BAt_%E0%11%22...\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Decoding-Strings-to-Text-or-Binary-Data","text":"Decoding Strings to Text or Binary Data","type":"heading","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String.percentDecoded() -> String"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"String.percentDecodedBytesArray() -> [UInt8]","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To decode a String containing percent-encoding, call the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecoded()"},{"text":" function, which decodes the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string to bytes and interprets them as Unicode text. If the decoded bytes do not contain Unicode text,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecodedBytesArray()"},{"text":" to retrieve the bytes as binary data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\"AC%2FDC\".percentDecoded()","\/\/ \"AC\/DC\"","\"%BAt_%E0%11%22\".percentDecodedBytesArray()","\/\/ [186, 116, 95, 224, 17, 34, ...]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Encoding-and-Decoding-Lazily","text":"Encoding and Decoding Lazily","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For certain algorithms, it can be useful to percent-encode binary data, or to read decoded binary data, lazily."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"WebURL adds "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentEncoded(using:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentDecoded()"},{"type":"text","text":" functions to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LazyCollection"},{"type":"text","text":", each returning view objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which encode and decode data on-demand."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://com.karwa.WebURL/documentation/WebURL/PercentEncodeSet/urlComponentSet":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The component percent-encode set. This set includes almost all special characters, making"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it suitable for encoding arbitrary strings at runtime for use in any URL component."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"key